Part 6: Best Practices & The Standard Library

6.1 Coding Style & Safety

· Use meaningful names, consistent indentation.
· Always initialise variables.
· Check return values of malloc, fopen, etc.
· Use const wherever applicable.
· Avoid gets(); use fgets instead.
· Use snprintf over sprintf.
· Compile with high warning levels (-Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic).

